===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|povre|lang=enm}}, {{term|povere|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} (and {{etyl|xno|en}}) {{term|povre|lang=fro}}, {{term|poure|lang=fro}} (Modern {{etyl|fr|-}} {{term|pauvre|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pauper|lang=la}} (English {{m|en|pauper}}), from {{etyl|itc-ola|en}} *{{m|itc-ola||pavo-pars|getting little}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ph₁w-||smallness}}. Cognate with {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|fēawa||little, few}}. Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|earm|lang=enm}}, {{term|arm||poor|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|earm|lang=ang}}; See [[arm#Etymology_2|arm]]), {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|wanstum|wantsum, wantsome|poor, needy|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|non|-}} {{m|non|vant||deficiency, lack, want}}, {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|unlede||poor|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|unlǣde}}, {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|unweli|unweli, unwely|poor, unwealthy|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|un-|lang=ang}} + {{m|ang|weliġ||well-to-do, prosperous, rich}}.

